This weekend’s ANC NEC meeting hasn't been short of drama. Suspended Secretary General, Ace Magashule and ANC MP, Bongani Bongo, were booted out of the virtual meeting. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC is investigating leaks from its ongoing National Executive Committee meeting. They include a clip of former president Thabo Mbeki asking the executive to reflect on the state of the governing party, and the allegations about the way it's implementing the contentious step-aside resolution. READ: ANC threatens action over NEC audio leaks The ANC says the recordings are being circulated to further a nefarious agenda, and those behind the leaks are guilty of misconduct. The party says its legal team is handling the matter. eNCA's senior reporter Aviwe Mtila shares more details in the video.